Description: Vera Bradley's Metro (or Metropolitan) bag was initially sold as a portfolio bag, geared toward businesswoman who carry around file folders and legal documents. It's large enough (and has a zipper) so it can be used to hold a laptop or a laptop inside of a laptop sleeve. The strap is long and the clasps are plastic, so it's lightweight, unlike many laptop or portfolio bags. There's a front pocket with a key fob and clip to hold your keys and plenty of pockets and zippers inside and in the back.
